			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				I will go so far as to say that this spell is nearly useless for anything<BR>
other than saving newbies caught in the middle of a mob.  It doesn't do<BR>
a particularly useful amount of damage, but it does seem to get the attention of<BR>
every monster close enough to smack you for your trouble.<BR>
<BR>
Wizards are not tanks.  Heheh.<BR>
<BR>
The LAST thing a wizard a sane wants to do with a group of several monsters is to be right in the middle of them<BR>
and make them all angry at *them*.  In fact, it's a great way to make sure you<BR>
can't cast another spell until the fight (one way or another) is over.  Ugh.<BR>

				</font>
			</td>

