	<tr>
		
			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				My opinion about that spell changed completely this week, because I noticed that Verant had FIXED the special EFX, so you don't get frustrated as before. It seems the spell affects up to 3 creatures, provided they are within melee range (I suspect those behind you can't be affected, unlike with Fingers of Fire). The damage/mana ratio is the best I know for an AE spell, i.e. when it is maxed it will do 31 damage per creature for 39 mana; if you affect 2 creatures, that is a ratio of 62/39 = 1.59, better than Shock spells (Shock of Ice 1.27 when maxed, Shock of Lightning 1.33 at level 14). It is a reasonable bonus for the risk you take by annoying several creatures at once.
				</font>
			</td>

	</tr>
	
